# Week 3 Progress Report: Motion Control and Software Integration

## Overview

-Week 3 focused on troubleshooting the Y-axis motion control system, integrating safety mechanisms, and testing software-based machine operation. Limit switch functionality was implemented for the X-axis, and motor control was verified using LaserGRBL. Initial laser module testing and system-level debugging activities were also carried out.

## Tasks Completed

- Integrated and tested an X-axis limit switch for homing and boundary protection.
- Performed initial testing of the laser module and laser driver.
- Investigated and tested multiple approaches to resolve Y-axis motor issues.
- Successfully controlled and jogged the X-axis motor using LaserGRBL.
- Assembled and tested eight soldering iron units for delivery.

## Challenges Faced

- The Y-axis stepper motor exhibited low-speed operation, oscillation, and unstable movement under continuous command inputs.
- Homing offset parameters were not functioning as expected, causing the limit switch to remain engaged and requiring system resets.
- Additional debugging was required to achieve reliable and repeatable machine motion.

## Key Outcomes

- Established software-based motor control through LaserGRBL.
- Implemented a functional limit switch mechanism for machine safety.
- Improved understanding of machine homing, motion control, and troubleshooting procedures.

## Next Steps

- Resolve Y-axis motor performance and stability issues.
- Optimize homing and limit switch behavior for reliable operation.
- Generate and engrave test images using LaserGRBL.
- Validate overall machine accuracy and repeatability.
